SUMMARY:Backpacking Talk-Round 2 Beginner to Advanced
DESCRIPTION:The Portland Hiking Meetup Group\nHi everyone\, if you were at the last meeting\, please come to this one as well\, if not\, please join us. I have a private room reserved at Steeplejack in NE Portland\, I think it will be a better forum for our discussions. We will have our own wait staff\, so we will have table service and can pay individual checks. So\, let's meet and discuss backpacking. Specifically\, we will talk about gear\, destinations and permits. Beginners to experts are welcome\, this includes people that are interested in backpacking\, but have never been on a trip yet. Bring your questions and experience to the table.\n\nI will be looking for volunteers this time to help secure some permits\, so be thinking about that. You will need to setup an account with recreation.gov to be able to help. We can discuss things related to gear\, what brands\, where to shop\, what to look for. We will talk about trip ideas and acquiring the proper permits to make the trip happen. We can also talk about other overnight trips like renting fire lookouts etc.\n\nWe will meet at Steeplejack on NE Broadway . Show up any time after 5. There will be a sign directing you to the room. The food and drinks here are really good. Okay\, I hope to see you out there.
